### Inventory Service API Testing
### This file can be used with the REST Client extension in VS Code
### to test the Inventory Service API endpoints

# Set the base URL (adjust port if needed)
@baseUrl = https://localhost:7297
@inventoryUrl = {{baseUrl}}/api/inventory

### Health Check (if available)
GET {{baseUrl}}/health

### Get All Inventory Items
GET {{inventoryUrl}}
Accept: application/json

### Get Inventory Item by ID
GET {{inventoryUrl}}/1
Accept: application/json

### Create New Inventory Item
POST {{inventoryUrl}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "name": "Test Product",
    "description": "A test product for the inventory",
    "quantity": 100,
    "price": 29.99,
    "category": "Electronics"
}

### Update Inventory Item
PUT {{inventoryUrl}}/1
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "id": 1,
    "name": "Updated Product",
    "description": "An updated test product",
    "quantity": 150,
    "price": 34.99,
    "category": "Electronics"
}

### Partially Update Inventory Item
PATCH {{inventoryUrl}}/1
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "quantity": 75
}

### Delete Inventory Item
DELETE {{inventoryUrl}}/1

### Search Inventory Items
GET {{inventoryUrl}}/search?query=test
Accept: application/json

### Get Inventory Items by Category
GET {{inventoryUrl}}/category/Electronics
Accept: application/json

### Get Low Stock Items (if endpoint exists)
GET {{inventoryUrl}}/low-stock
Accept: application/json

